{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01X6ypFV66YbzbVniwG4MQGR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Build user profile page\n     2→\n     3→## Completion Notes\n     4→- Created `/user/[username]` profile page with avatar (initial fallback), display name, username, bio, stats\n     5→- Added tabbed sections for user's themes and starred themes, reusing ThemeCard style\n     6→- Profile owner gets \"Edit Profile\" button for inline editing of display name and bio\n     7→- Added author name links on homepage ThemeCards (with stopPropagation) and theme detail page\n     8→- Handles loading and not-found states; consistent header with ThemeDrops logo, CreateThemeLink, AuthControls\n     9→- Build passes cleanly\n    10→\n    11→## Context\n    12→The PLAN says \"Users should have a profile page similar to like a youtube profile.\" The backend already has all the queries needed (`users.getByUsername`, `themes.getByAuthor`, `stars.getStarredThemes`, `users.updateProfile`), but there is no frontend page. Author names on the homepage gallery cards and theme detail page are plain text — not links. This is a critical MVP gap: users who create themes have no public presence on the site.\n    13→\n    14→## Requirements\n    15→\n    16→### 1. Create the profile page route at `app/src/app/user/[username]/page.tsx`\n    17→- Fetch user by username via `api.users.getByUsername`\n    18→- Show 404-style message if user not found\n    19→- Display: avatar (or initial fallback), display name, username, bio\n    20→- Show the user's public themes using `api.themes.getByAuthor` in a grid of ThemeCards (reuse the same card style as the homepage)\n    21→- Show the user's starred themes using `api.stars.getStarredThemes` in a separate tab or section\n    22→- Include theme count and star count stats\n    23→- If the viewer is the profile owner, show an \"Edit Profile\" button that allows editing displayName and bio via `api.users.updateProfile`\n    24→\n    25→### 2. Make author names link to profiles\n    26→- **Homepage (`app/src/app/page.tsx`)**: The author name in `ThemeCard` should link to `/user/{username}`. The `useQuery(api.users.get, ...)` call already returns username — wrap the author name in a `<Link>`.\n    27→- **Theme detail page (`app/src/app/theme/[slug]/page.tsx`)**: The \"by {author}\" line should link to `/user/{username}`.\n    28→- Links should use `event.stopPropagation()` or be nested correctly so clicking the author name navigates to the profile, not the theme.\n    29→\n    30→### 3. Include site header consistency\n    31→- Use the same header pattern as the theme detail page (ThemeDrops logo link, CreateThemeLink, AuthControls).\n    32→\n    33→## Backend queries already available\n    34→- `users.getByUsername({ username })` — returns full user doc\n    35→- `users.getCurrentUser()` — returns current signed-in user\n    36→- `users.updateProfile({ displayName?, bio?, avatarUrl? })` — mutation\n    37→- `themes.getByAuthor({ authorId })` — returns user's themes (filters private unless viewer is owner)\n    38→- `stars.getStarredThemes({ userId })` — returns themes the user has starred\n    39→\n    40→## Important notes\n    41→- `users.get` (used on homepage cards) returns `{ _id, username, displayName, avatarUrl }` — username is already available for building the link URL\n    42→- The `getByUsername` query returns the full user doc including `bio` — but does NOT filter sensitive fields. Only display: `_id`, `username`, `displayName`, `bio`, `avatarUrl`.\n    43→- Keep the design consistent with the existing pages (gray-50 bg, white cards, same typography scale)\n    44→- The profile page should look good even if the user has zero themes\n    45→\n    46→## Acceptance criteria\n    47→- [ ] `/user/{username}` renders a profile page with user info and their themes\n    48→- [ ] Visiting a non-existent username shows a \"User not found\" message\n    49→- [ ] Author names on homepage cards link to `/user/{username}`\n    50→- [ ] Author name on theme detail page links to `/user/{username}`\n    51→- [ ] Profile owner can edit their display name and bio inline\n    52→- [ ] Page includes consistent site header with nav back to home\n    53→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ec90dcd9-bd24-4490-bfb2-b14990aaa276","uuid":"e4bc9fa1-e49b-4855-92a0-b166af6bd5b0","timestamp":"2026-03-28T00:09:42.831Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/matt/code/themedrops/swarm/tasks/user-profile-page.reviewing.md","content":"# Build user profile page\n\n## Completion Notes\n- Created `/user/[username]` profile page with avatar (initial fallback), display name, username, bio, stats\n- Added tabbed sections for user's themes and starred themes, reusing ThemeCard style\n- Profile owner gets \"Edit Profile\" button for inline editing of display name and bio\n- Added author name links on homepage ThemeCards (with stopPropagation) and theme detail page\n- Handles loading and not-found states; consistent header with ThemeDrops logo, CreateThemeLink, AuthControls\n- Build passes cleanly\n\n## Context\nThe PLAN says \"Users should have a profile page similar to like a youtube profile.\" The backend already has all the queries needed (`users.getByUsername`, `themes.getByAuthor`, `stars.getStarredThemes`, `users.updateProfile`), but there is no frontend page. Author names on the homepage gallery cards and theme detail page are plain text — not links. This is a critical MVP gap: users who create themes have no public presence on the site.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### 1. Create the profile page route at `app/src/app/user/[username]/page.tsx`\n- Fetch user by username via `api.users.getByUsername`\n- Show 404-style message if user not found\n- Display: avatar (or initial fallback), display name, username, bio\n- Show the user's public themes using `api.themes.getByAuthor` in a grid of ThemeCards (reuse the same card style as the homepage)\n- Show the user's starred themes using `api.stars.getStarredThemes` in a separate tab or section\n- Include theme count and star count stats\n- If the viewer is the profile owner, show an \"Edit Profile\" button that allows editing displayName and bio via `api.users.updateProfile`\n\n### 2. Make author names link to profiles\n- **Homepage (`app/src/app/page.tsx`)**: The author name in `ThemeCard` should link to `/user/{username}`. The `useQuery(api.users.get, ...)` call already returns username — wrap the author name in a `<Link>`.\n- **Theme detail page (`app/src/app/theme/[slug]/page.tsx`)**: The \"by {author}\" line should link to `/user/{username}`.\n- Links should use `event.stopPropagation()` or be nested correctly so clicking the author name navigates to the profile, not the theme.\n\n### 3. Include site header consistency\n- Use the same header pattern as the theme detail page (ThemeDrops logo link, CreateThemeLink, AuthControls).\n\n## Backend queries already available\n- `users.getByUsername({ username })` — returns full user doc\n- `users.getCurrentUser()` — returns current signed-in user\n- `users.updateProfile({ displayName?, bio?, avatarUrl? })` — mutation\n- `themes.getByAuthor({ authorId })` — returns user's themes (filters private unless viewer is owner)\n- `stars.getStarredThemes({ userId })` — returns themes the user has starred\n\n## Important notes\n- `users.get` (used on homepage cards) returns `{ _id, username, displayName, avatarUrl }` — username is already available for building the link URL\n- The `getByUsername` query returns the full user doc including `bio` — but does NOT filter sensitive fields. Only display: `_id`, `username`, `displayName`, `bio`, `avatarUrl`.\n- Keep the design consistent with the existing pages (gray-50 bg, white cards, same typography scale)\n- The profile page should look good even if the user has zero themes\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `/user/{username}` renders a profile page with user info and their themes\n- [ ] Visiting a non-existent username shows a \"User not found\" message\n- [ ] Author names on homepage cards link to `/user/{username}`\n- [ ] Author name on theme detail page links to `/user/{username}`\n- [ ] Profile owner can edit their display name and bio inline\n- [ ] Page includes consistent site header with nav back to home\n","numLines":53,"startLine":1,"totalLines":53}}}
